creator: TalkLife Ltd
descriptionHtml:
If you're struggling you can get support right now! TalkLife connects you with real people around the world who want to listen and support you. No judgement. Just support! Let's talk!

Life isn't always smooth sailing, but you're not alone! At TalkLife you can instantly meet supportive people who actually care and want to listen! Share what's on your mind and get the help you need today! Meet new friends who really get you, You're not alone!

At TalkLife, we’re here for the moments when you just need a friend and some advice! We have a large community receiving support across anxiety, depression, eating disorders and those battling self harm.

If you're battling with mental health, perhaps even struggling with self harm it can feel lonely, It can suck, and let’s admit it: that’s tough to say out loud. We all know that, and maybe, sometimes, we’ve just been made to feel a little afraid to say it. TalkLife is here for everyone and anyone who just needs someone to talk to. Who just needs someone to listen. Because, hey, we all do.

So get on TalkLife and talk to people going through the exact same struggles you are. We know that sometimes it’s sort of hard to talk about certain things with family or even friends. This is a safe place where you can talk about anything: mental health, depression, self harm, eating disorders, a bad breakup or a relationship, school or work...it doesn’t matter. If you want to talk about it, someone else, does too. No judgments. No bullying. Just people who get you.

Look, we made TalkLife because we wanted to create a community where you can always feel welcome and know that someone is here for you. Literally thousands of people are always on TalkLife-- at any time -- just waiting to listen. We think that’s pretty cool. Sometimes, life’s too darn hard to go through alone. We’d all feel a little better if we just felt safe and heard. So come join us and Download TalkLife for free today and make right now and everything after it a little bit better. Let’s talk and figure this life thing out together.

Share life’s ups and downs
• Talk about life’s struggles in a safe and supportive environment. No bullies here. And we’re silly serious about that.
• Help new friends out by sharing tips and advice from your own experiences. It’s amazing how helpful you can be to someone out there, whether you ever knew it or not.
• Open up or post anonymously – it’s totally up to you. However you want to talk? We let you do it just that way.

Get involved with a community of thousands of people just like you
• Personally chat with or send gifts to other TalkLife users you find common ground with.
• Read and comment on interesting and inspirational content from the TalkLife blog. We honestly wanna hear from you!

descriptionHtml:

You may feel bad now, but you're not alone, and there are better times ahead. TalkLife is here for you through the shiny and the muck, and they can really lift you. Download TalkLife and say hello.

Download TalkLife and you can safely talk about any struggles and reach support across many areas including, anxiety, self-harm, living with depression, self harm, loneliness, PTSD, bipolar, suicidal thoughts, and many more.

*Please note, if you are in a crisis situation, please seek emergency support as soon as possible. Peer support should not be used if you are in an emergency situation.

TalkLife is all about support. Our community is full of people who have also felt alone, battled depression or living with anxiety and needed somewhere safe to talk. TalkLife is a positive community where people have real conversations about how they feel - lonely, misunderstood, unhappy, or actually feeling alright.

People use TalkLife to seek support for the bad times, but also celebrate the good ones. You, your thoughts, your feelings are important - don't keep them bottled up. You can even vent anonymously.

You may feel bad now, but you're not alone, and there are better times ahead. TalkLife is here for you through the shiny and the muck, and they can really lift you. Download TalkLife and say hello.

Download TalkLife and you can safely talk about any struggles and reach support across many areas including, anxiety, self-harm, living with depression, loneliness, PTSD, bipolar, suicidal thoughts, and many more.

*Please note, if you are in a crisis situation, please seek emergency support as soon as possible. Peer support should not be used if you are in an emergency situation.

People use TalkLife to seek support for the bad times, but also celebrate the good ones. You, your thoughts, your feelings are important - don't keep them bottled up. You can even vent anonymously.

creator: TalkLife Ltd
descriptionHtml:
Millions of people just like you are connecting on TalkLife everyday. It's your go-to place to talk about anything and everything judgment free - the tough times and the good stuff too. Dealing with anxiety, struggling with depression or just in a rough patch? You'll find people just like you who understand exactly what you're going through. TalkLife is all about real talk and real support. Feel like you’re having a panic attack at 3 AM, desperate for some shut eye but suffering insomnia, need to vent anonymously or share a win? This community is here for you, offering a listening ear and a place to belong, whenever you need it.

Why TalkLife?

- Focused on mental health: This app was built by people who've walked in your shoes and know the power of connecting with like-minded people.
- Anonymous: You no longer have to feel scared to express yourself freely. Talk about your fears, loneliness and insecurities without being judged.
- The shiny and the muck: Feeling down, ashamed or isolated today? Share it with us. Tomorrow you might feel better after talking about it. We're here to listen, every step of the way.
- Make genuine friends: Lifelong friendships are forged daily with users across the world, making our support community pretty amazing. We’re constantly overwhelmed by the incredible stories from our users - from feeling lonely, nervous and not enough, to being surrounded by positive community support every day.
- Always available: TalkLife is a free, global support network, here for you 24/7. If you're battling with your mental health, perhaps even struggling with self harm or suicidal thoughts, it can feel incredibly lonely but just know there are people on TalkLife who have been where you are and want to help.

App Features

- Peer support: Connect with our amazing global & diverse community that will fill your cup.
- Safe space: Moderated to ensure a safe and positive place to express yourself.
- Journaling/Diary Feature: Keep track of your thoughts and progress.
- Emotion and mental health tracker: Understand your mood & emotions by tracking this is in the Wellness Centre.
- Public & Private Groups: Join or create groups that resonate with you.
- Direct Messaging: Have private conversations with people who get you.
- Group Chat: Engage in lively discussions with the TalkLife community.

NEW: Wellness Centre

We’ve just launched the Wellness Centre where you can access free mental health resources like self-care tips and self-directed learning modules. Learn what makes you tick with coping strategies and form habits that could help you to stop & breathe when life gets hard. Current modules include: Depression, Social Anxiety, Managing Worry, Panic Attacks, Health Anxiety, OCD and PTSD. Coming soon: ADHD, Eating Disorders, Bipolar, Insomnia, Stress & Grief.

Download TalkLife Today

Get TalkLife and make friends, share your story and be part of a community who share the same experiences as you. Your thoughts and feelings are always valued here. Life is filled with a barrage of background noise - TalkLife is a free mental health app for when it all becomes too much.

About TalkLife

Making mental health discussions easy and relatable has always been our motivation. Our goal is to ensure no one feels alone in their mental health journey.

Praises for TalkLife

- “I literally just downloaded this app but I am blown away by the support from everyone and for everyone. Life is hard and it’s great that we can get through it with each other” - User Review
- “Anxiety and depression is a constant struggle but apps like this let you know you are not going through it alone” - User Review
- "Young people need somewhere to talk about youth mental health. TalkLife is that place” - Stephen Fry

TalkLife is free to download with optional in-app purchases. Not an ad in sight, just compassion and emotional support.

Emergency Note

In crisis? Please seek immediate professional help. TalkLife offers peer support, not emergency services.

We’re constantly overwhelmed by the incredible stories from our users - from feeling lonely, nervous and not enough, to being surrounded by positive community support every day.

- Peer support: Connect with our amazing global & diverse community that will fill your cup.

Learn what makes you tick with coping strategies and form habits that could help you to stop & breathe when life gets hard. Current modules include: Depression, Social Anxiety, Managing Worry, Panic Attacks, Health Anxiety, OCD and PTSD. Coming soon: ADHD, Eating Disorders, Bipolar, Insomnia, Stress & Grief.

About TalkLife

Making mental health discussions easy and relatable has always been our motivation. Our goal is to ensure no one feels alone in their mental health journey.

TalkLife is free to download with optional in-app purchases. Not an ad in sight, just compassion and emotional support.

In crisis? Please seek immediate professional help. TalkLife offers peer support, not emergency services.
